<div class="container">
    <section class="intro">
        <h1>All About Snowboarding</h1>
        <div class="grid">
            <div class="grid-item">
                <img src="~/img/220210090823-01-jeremy-jones-protect-our-winters-c2e-story-card.jpg" alt="Image Description" />
            </div>
            <div class="grid-item">
                <p>
                    Snowboarding, a dynamic and exhilarating winter sport, has a rich history that traces back to the 1960s in the United States. Initially conceived as a hybrid of skiing, surfing, and skateboarding, it was the brainchild of thrill-seekers looking to bring the excitement of surfing to the snow. The sport saw a significant evolution over the decades, moving from a niche pastime to a mainstream winter activity. Snowboarding's inclusion in the Winter Olympics in 1998 solidified its status as a globally recognized sport. Today, it continues to captivate enthusiasts with its blend of speed, creativity, and the sheer joy of gliding across snowy landscapes.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="why-snowboarding">
        <h2>Why Snowboarding?</h2>
        <div class="grid">
            <div class="grid-item">
                <p>
                    Snowboarding stands out for its thrill and the unparalleled sense of freedom it offers on the slopes. It caters to a wide range of styles, each appealing to different types of riders:
                </p>
            </div>
            <div class="grid-item">
                <ul>
                    <li>Freestyle: Known for its tricks and jumps, freestyle snowboarding is about creativity and flair in terrain parks.</li>
                    <li>Freeride: This style is all about exploring the mountain's natural terrain, offering an adventurous ride down unmarked slopes.</li>
                    <li>Alpine: Focused on speed and precision, alpine snowboarding involves carving down groomed runs on hard-packed snow.</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="getting-started">
        <h3>Getting Started</h3>
        <div class="grid">
            <div class="grid-item">
                <img src="~/img/istockphoto-1446438866-612x612.jpg" alt="Image Description" />
            </div>
            <div class="grid-item">
                <p>
                    For beginners eager to dive into the world of snowboarding, starting on the right foot is crucial. Here are some tips to ensure a smooth and enjoyable introduction to the sport:
                </p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Gear Recommendations: Invest in quality gear suited for beginners, including a forgiving snowboard, comfortable boots, and appropriate bindings. Safety gear, such as helmets and wrist guards, is also essential.</li>
                    <li>Finding a Good Snowboarding School: Lessons from a certified instructor can accelerate your learning curve, helping you master the basics and avoid common mistakes. Look for schools with positive reviews and experienced instructors.</li>
                    <li>Safety Tips: Always stay within your comfort zone and follow the mountain's safety rules. Learning how to fall correctly can minimize the risk of injury, and staying aware of your surroundings helps avoid collisions.</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>
</div>
